  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Boulard Owner-Driven Housing Repairs and Latrine Construction</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Families</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MCC is working with ACCESS to support 40 families in Boulard as they repair their homes into hazard-resistant houses using Owner-Driven-Housing (ODHR) techniques. This project is also working towards supporting these families to start or improve their small businesses.Thirdly, 10 families are being assisted as they build environmentally sound latrines. After the 2010 earthquake, the need for quality housing remains one of the greatest challenges to recovery; ODHR empowers families to make informed decisions regarding their community&apos;s rehabilitation. Participating families are trained in quality standards for building and sanitation and are also learning how to work with builders to ensure they can manage reconstruction with technical assistance.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Participating families are being trained in hazard-resistant building techniques and basic conflict resolution and hygiene/sanitation awareness. Refresher training will also be held for builders (reviewing 2010 training). Families will receive a flat rate to support small business or begin one. ACCESS will meet with the participants to discuss business plans individually per family and cover the ways in which a family can either grow their business or start a business.</narrative>
  </description>
